Past a certain limit, a nuclear device will simply blow a hole up thru the atmosphere. The surface will act as a reflector, bouncing the energy back up through the hole. (Not that nasty things would not result, but only that blowing up a planet isn't easy. Making it uninhabitable maybe, rubble no.)<br>
<br>
A crude rule of thumb is that a nuclear weapon will vaporize roughly the equal to its yield.<br>
<br>
Thus a one gigaton deeply buried device will very roughly vaporize a gigaton of rock.<br>
